Then it occurred to me that whereas distance running legend Eliud Kipchoge will have to contend with running over 42 kilometres for at least two hours in search of gold medal at the Olympics, others will actually dance their way to Olympic gold medals!
On Monday, IOC announced the addition of four new sports – breakdancing, skateboarding, sport climbing and surfing - to the 2024 Olympics. Whereas skateboarding, sport climbing and surfing will debut at the 2020 Olympics which will take place in Tokyo from July 23 next year, breakdancing will make its entry to the Olympics in 2024.



