The IOC said the changes were aimed at making the Olympic Games appeal to a younger audience. The acrobatic dance battles will be known as “breaking” at the Olympics.
Immediately the announcement was made, Australian squash legend Michelle Martin said the Olympics have become a mockery.
“It’s sort of making a mockery of what the Olympics is. When you look at what it all used to stand for, the Olympics, it definitely fits in the category.  What does the Olympics stand for these days, I don’t really know. They either need to go back to what the Olympics was about and let the other sports stay outside of that because the problem is it’s having such an impact on the sports that don’t get into the Olympics now. The Olympics has lost what it was. Yes, they’re trying to move with the times but it’s creating a mockery of the thing,” Martin told British media.



