In 2008, IOC permitted a wushu (Chinese martial art which is a complete contact sport) tournament to run parallel to the 2008 Beijing Olympics rather than being trialed as part of the Olympics.
Creating a category separate from the Olympics to reward excellence in breakdancing will solve the matter.
